senses.sense_text:
(as a connective) and; (connecting and continuing) and then, then; (as a disjuntive) but, yet, however; (as an adv.) also, even, likewise 
(1) and, Mt. 2:2, 3, 11; 4:22) 
(2) και και, both and; 
(3) as a cumulative particle, also, too, Mt. 5:39; Jn. 8:19; 1Cor. 11:6; 
(4) emphatic, even, also, Mt. 10:30; 1Cor. 2:10; in NT adversative, but, Mt. 11:19; also introductory of the apodosis of a sentence, Gal. 3:28; Jas. 2:4
